<example id="fs-idp173892208">
<para id="fs-idp155406304"><title>Determination of Δ<emphasis effect="italics">S</emphasis>°</title>
Calculate the standard entropy change for the following process:</para>
<equation id="fs-idp582800"><m:math><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mtext>H</m:mtext><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub><m:mtext>O</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>g</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">⟶</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:msub><m:mtext>H</m:mtext><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub><m:mtext>O</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>l</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></equation>
<para id="fs-idp180269712"><title>Solution</title>
Calculate the entropy change using standard entropies as shown above:</para>
<equation id="fs-idm7244112"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>Δ</m:mi><m:mi>S</m:mi><m:mo>°</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>mol</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>70.0</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>J</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:msup><m:mrow><m:mtext>mol</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>−</m:mtext><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:msup><m:mtext>K</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>−</m:mtext><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>mol</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>188.8</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>J</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:msup><m:mrow><m:mtext>mol</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>−</m:mtext><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:msup><m:mtext>K</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>−</m:mtext><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mtext>−</m:mtext><m:mn>118.8</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>J/K</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math></equation>
<para id="fs-idm47317216">The value for Δ<emphasis effect="italics">S</emphasis>° is negative, as expected for this phase transition (condensation), which the previous section discussed.</para>
<para id="fs-idp319200"><title>Check Your Learning</title>
